WEBVTT

01:02.125 --> 01:05.208
Hannah:
Oh, my God, he really
knew so many people.

01:05.208 --> 01:07.458
It's just crazy that
you don't know the depth

01:07.458 --> 01:09.125
of someone's power
until their funeral.

01:09.125 --> 01:11.959
It's so sad.

01:11.959 --> 01:13.291
Oh, my God.

01:13.291 --> 01:15.625
I think I see
Zadie Smith.

01:15.625 --> 01:17.083
That is definitely her.

01:17.083 --> 01:19.625
All right, calm down, kid.
It's a funeral.

01:24.667 --> 01:27.834
Who do you know here?

01:27.834 --> 01:31.667
Uh, that's David's
assistant, Bob.

01:46.458 --> 01:48.917
- Hi, Bob.
- Oh.

01:48.917 --> 01:50.291
I'm so sorry
for your loss.

01:50.291 --> 01:51.667
Oh, hi, Hannah.
Thank you.

01:51.667 --> 01:53.250
Woman:
Oh, Bob.

01:53.250 --> 01:56.834
Bob.
Sweet, sweet Bob.

01:56.834 --> 01:59.333
What would I do
without you?

02:00.625 --> 02:02.041
Hi, I'm Adam.

02:02.041 --> 02:04.542
- Oh, hi, Adam.
- Hi.

02:04.542 --> 02:05.834
- Hi.
- This is Hannah.

02:05.834 --> 02:08.458
- Hannah, hi.
- A pleasure to make
your acquaintance.

02:08.458 --> 02:09.834
I'm Annaliese.

02:09.834 --> 02:12.875
Oh, you haven't met.
This is David's wife.

02:12.875 --> 02:15.375
- ( whimpers )
- Oh, you're--

02:15.375 --> 02:17.083
you're David's wife, yes.

02:17.083 --> 02:20.542
- So, you two
lived together...
- Yes.

02:20.542 --> 02:23.875
...romantically
as well as maritally.

02:23.875 --> 02:27.041
I'm sorry, I-- how did
you know my husband?

02:27.041 --> 02:29.875
- This one.
- Uh, yes, I was writing
my memoir for him.

02:29.875 --> 02:31.166
Okay.

02:32.083 --> 02:33.708
Oh.

02:33.708 --> 02:34.959
Oh, my gosh.

02:34.959 --> 02:37.583
Oh, I know exactly
who you are.

02:37.583 --> 02:41.250
David spoke about you
all the time.

02:41.250 --> 02:43.208
- He did?
- He did.

02:43.208 --> 02:44.875
Oh, gosh,
he loved you.

02:44.875 --> 02:47.208
He really loved you
so much.

02:47.208 --> 02:48.750
You know, he always
would tell me

02:48.750 --> 02:50.959
about this amazing girl
that I needed to meet

02:50.959 --> 02:54.375
who would overcome
such obstacles.

02:54.375 --> 02:57.083
And now, finally,
I am meeting you.

02:57.083 --> 03:00.250
Thank you.
Well, my OCD is
very much in check now--

03:00.250 --> 03:02.542
But the Tourette's
and the obesity--

03:02.542 --> 03:04.291
Oh, no, no, no, no, no.
That was Paige.

03:04.291 --> 03:06.917
- What?
- That wasn't Hannah.
That was Paige.

03:06.917 --> 03:08.208
- Not Hannah.
- Oh.

03:08.208 --> 03:11.458
- Obesity?
- Um, no, no, no.

03:11.458 --> 03:13.750
- I don't have Tourette's.
- I'm so sorry.

03:13.750 --> 03:15.959
- I don't know about obesity...
- If everyone could
take their seats.

03:15.959 --> 03:18.166
I've always thought
I was more chubby
than obese.

03:18.166 --> 03:20.708
No, no, no, overcame.
It's my-- I'm so sorry.

03:20.708 --> 03:22.083
- It's nice meeting you.
- No, please.

03:22.083 --> 03:23.917
It's very nice to--
Bob, where are we headed?

03:23.917 --> 03:25.708
- Thank you.
- Where are we seated?

03:32.959 --> 03:34.750
( whispers )
I thought you said
he was gay.

03:34.750 --> 03:36.375
( whispering )
Well, I don't know now.

03:36.375 --> 03:38.083
He had gay apps
on his iPhone

03:38.083 --> 03:39.625
and he liked
to show his ankles,

03:39.625 --> 03:42.625
but what does that even mean
in this day and age?

03:42.625 --> 03:45.542
Priest:
Hello, everyone.
I am Father Tudor Snowdon.

03:45.542 --> 03:50.208
Today we celebrate the life
of David Pressler-Goings.

03:50.208 --> 03:53.458
( music playing )

03:56.291 --> 03:58.667
Can we go now, please?

03:58.667 --> 04:01.875
I'm not leaving
until I have locked eyes
with Michiko Kakutani.

04:01.875 --> 04:03.166
I told you that.

04:03.166 --> 04:05.000
Adam:
I'm gonna wait outside.

04:05.000 --> 04:06.917
Hannah:
Okay.

04:09.125 --> 04:10.917
Hi again.

04:10.917 --> 04:13.542
Oh, hi.

04:13.542 --> 04:14.667
- Hannah.
- Right.

04:14.667 --> 04:16.750
- Not Paige, Hannah.
- I know.

04:16.750 --> 04:18.959
- I know, I'm sorry.
- No, don't be.

04:18.959 --> 04:21.834
I was surprised that David
had such a beautiful--

04:21.834 --> 04:24.834
just stunningly--

04:24.834 --> 04:26.834
You thought he was gay.

04:26.834 --> 04:28.917
- Uh, no.
- Yes, you did.

04:28.917 --> 04:30.917
- No, I didn't.
- Yes, you did.
It's okay, it's okay.

04:30.917 --> 04:32.959
- I didn't. I thought
he was straight.
- It's okay.

04:32.959 --> 04:35.125
I thought he was straight.
I thought he wanted
to sleep with me.

04:35.125 --> 04:38.166
- Really, I know you--
- I mean, I wouldn't have
slept with him, but--

04:38.166 --> 04:39.542
A lot of people
think it.

04:39.542 --> 04:41.917
A lot of people
think he was gay.

04:41.917 --> 04:43.542
Well, he acted gay.

04:43.542 --> 04:46.667
And, you know,
he was...

04:46.667 --> 04:48.083
- sometimes.
- Okay.

04:48.083 --> 04:50.208
I loved working
with your husband.

04:50.208 --> 04:53.291
- David was wonderful.
- Oh, I bet.

04:53.291 --> 04:55.125
I mean, I know.

04:55.125 --> 04:58.792
Um... I'm working
on a book with David, too.

04:58.792 --> 05:00.250
I was. Was.

05:00.250 --> 05:01.834
I really hope
you finish the book,

05:01.834 --> 05:03.792
and I really, really hope
I get to read it someday.

05:03.792 --> 05:05.333
Thank you.
Yeah, I don't know.

05:05.333 --> 05:08.875
I mean, now that
Millstreet has dropped
all of David's projects,

05:08.875 --> 05:10.250
I just--

05:10.250 --> 05:12.625
I'd have to find
a new publisher, so,
you know, we'll see--

05:12.625 --> 05:15.291
Wait, you said
Millstreet's dropped
all of David's projects?

05:15.291 --> 05:17.708
Yeah-- oh, shit.
Shit.

05:17.708 --> 05:19.583
There's David's mom.
She's so devastated.

05:19.583 --> 05:21.834
- Have you seen Pepper?
Did you meet her?
- No, I didn't, no.

05:21.834 --> 05:23.583
- She's devastated
and I should--
- You were saying that--

05:23.583 --> 05:25.959
you were saying that
Millstreet's dropped
all of David's projects?

05:25.959 --> 05:28.375
Right, that's right.
For now, yeah.

05:28.375 --> 05:30.208
So my book is dead?

05:31.792 --> 05:32.708
Um...

05:32.708 --> 05:34.792
Do you happen to know
another publisher

05:34.792 --> 05:37.583
that I could maybe
slip the manuscript to

05:37.583 --> 05:39.583
if I do decide
that I really want to

05:39.583 --> 05:42.875
try to keep it alive?

05:46.250 --> 05:49.792
Okay, um, if I do
give you another name,

05:49.792 --> 05:52.291
will you get the fuck
out of here?

05:54.083 --> 05:55.625
Yes.

05:55.625 --> 05:57.750
Great.

05:57.750 --> 05:59.250
Great, I'll be back.

05:59.250 --> 06:02.250
Honestly, I just--

06:02.250 --> 06:04.500
I loved your husband.

06:04.500 --> 06:06.166
You know the person
who gave me this

06:06.166 --> 06:10.667
told me that
it used to belong
to Edna St. Vincent Millay.

06:10.667 --> 06:13.250
But who can ever know
if that's true?

06:13.250 --> 06:16.208
Can you believe that
my friend told me
that she died

06:16.208 --> 06:18.000
so that she didn't
have to hang out
with me?

06:18.000 --> 06:20.291
Yeah, no,
I totally get that.

06:20.291 --> 06:21.625
Excuse me?

06:21.625 --> 06:23.959
Okay, look,
I know that we, like,
technically live together,

06:23.959 --> 06:26.250
but this is still
very much my private home

06:26.250 --> 06:28.291
and it just is slightly
worrisome to me

06:28.291 --> 06:29.959
that all you do
all day long

06:29.959 --> 06:31.917
is sit around and watch
"The Forensic Files."

06:31.917 --> 06:33.125
And I have kept
my mouth shut until now,

06:33.125 --> 06:35.792
but I literally cannot
keep my mouth shut any longer

06:35.792 --> 06:39.166
because I really
need to study.

06:39.959 --> 06:41.750
- Since when?
- Since forever!

06:41.750 --> 06:44.834
Plus, my recent hijinks
have really taken
a toll on my GPA.

06:45.959 --> 06:48.291
But I thought this was
your time to go wild

06:48.291 --> 06:51.125
before you become
an international
business lady.

06:51.125 --> 06:53.583
Yeah, exactly,
so it's really important
to my 15-year plan

06:53.583 --> 06:55.000
that I get into
a good business school

06:55.000 --> 06:57.208
because I don't want to
become like all my friends
and family,

06:57.208 --> 06:59.542
yourself included,
no offense.

06:59.542 --> 07:01.458
What happens after
the 15-year plan?

07:01.458 --> 07:03.375
It would be, like, insane
to think about that.

07:06.333 --> 07:07.834
Oh, yes.

07:07.834 --> 07:09.458
Yes, I could definitely
come in tomorrow.

07:09.458 --> 07:11.375
Adam:
...conditioner later
and then it's deodorant.

07:11.375 --> 07:13.583
Caroline: Why? Why?
Why are you inherently
disinclined

07:13.583 --> 07:14.792
to support me in any way?

07:14.792 --> 07:16.708
- Adam: You're living
in my house.
- Oh, God!

07:16.708 --> 07:18.875
Thank you so much.
I will see you then.

07:18.875 --> 07:21.125
- I really appreciate it.
- ( argument continues )

07:21.125 --> 07:22.458
Why should I give
you anything?

07:22.458 --> 07:24.625
Oh, right, God forbid.
God forbid we assist
one another, right?

07:24.625 --> 07:26.500
- Simply because we share
the same blood.
- Guys...

07:26.500 --> 07:28.000
Forget about the fact
that I spent

07:28.000 --> 07:29.542
my formative years
raising you because Verna

07:29.542 --> 07:31.500
- had absolutely no interest.
- No, I never asked you
for anything.

07:31.500 --> 07:33.083
- No one ever asked you
for anything.
- Oh, please.

07:33.083 --> 07:34.417
You can't be bothered
to do anything for anybody.

07:34.417 --> 07:35.792
You need something
from everyone all the time--

07:35.792 --> 07:38.583
( screams )
Whoa!

07:38.583 --> 07:40.542
Oh, my God.

07:40.542 --> 07:42.041
Seriously.

07:42.041 --> 07:44.875
Seriously, it's already been
a very long day for me,

07:44.875 --> 07:47.041
and what I need
is a peaceful house

07:47.041 --> 07:48.583
where people
are centered.

07:48.583 --> 07:50.083
See what you're doing,
Caroline?

07:50.083 --> 07:52.250
You're upsetting Hannah
when she just found out
her book is dead.

07:52.250 --> 07:54.250
I actually just found out
I have a very exciting meeting

07:54.250 --> 07:56.875
with a publisher who I think
is pretty interested.

07:56.875 --> 07:58.375
I was just trying
to make myself a meal.

07:58.375 --> 08:00.458
- Just feeding myself--
- With my last eggs.

08:00.458 --> 08:04.041
Guys, I cannot take
this anymore, okay?

08:04.041 --> 08:05.417
We have to work
this out.

08:05.417 --> 08:07.041
There is no
working this out.

08:07.041 --> 08:09.125
Okay, I've watched enough
"Dr. Phils" and "Interventions"

08:09.125 --> 08:12.458
to know you can
work anything out
if you talk about it.

08:12.458 --> 08:13.542
I would love to.

08:13.542 --> 08:16.291
Thank you, Caroline.
I appreciate that.

08:16.291 --> 08:17.583
Adam?

08:17.583 --> 08:20.708
Will you join us
at the listening table?

08:21.792 --> 08:24.750
- Please?
- ( laughs )

08:25.834 --> 08:27.333
Come on.

08:27.333 --> 08:29.417
Thank you.

08:30.708 --> 08:33.417
Okay, I think
we should all start

08:33.417 --> 08:37.082
by acknowledging
that we all really care
about each other.

08:37.082 --> 08:39.375
So, Caroline,
tell me you love me.

08:39.375 --> 08:40.750
Hannah, I love you.

08:40.750 --> 08:43.667
I love you, too.
Adam, you tell me
you love me.

08:43.667 --> 08:45.917
Why are we telling you
we love you?

08:45.917 --> 08:48.375
( sighs )
Okay, so then
why don't you both

08:48.375 --> 08:50.208
just tell each other
that you love each other?

08:50.208 --> 08:51.792
- Adam, I love you.
- This is dumb.

08:51.792 --> 08:53.750
Hannah:
Okay, emotions are
running high right now,

08:53.750 --> 08:55.375
and I think
it's really important

08:55.375 --> 08:57.417
that we avoid using
inflammatory language--

08:57.417 --> 08:58.875
words like "dumb,"

08:58.875 --> 09:01.667
words like "skank,"
"fatty."

09:01.667 --> 09:04.500
Let's just acknowledge
that we're here
for each other

09:04.500 --> 09:06.291
and make this
a safe space.

09:06.291 --> 09:07.542
So, Adam, why don't
you just begin

09:07.542 --> 09:10.583
by telling Caroline
what some of your issues
are with her

09:10.583 --> 09:13.166
in a very calm,
rational way?

09:15.375 --> 09:19.959
I feel like
she's an evil person

09:19.959 --> 09:23.750
who pukes on everything,
metaphorically.

09:23.750 --> 09:26.917
Okay, maybe perhaps
you could elaborate on that...

09:26.917 --> 09:28.834
- Jeez.
- ...and be a little bit
more specific

09:28.834 --> 09:30.834
with some of your
issues with me.

09:30.834 --> 09:32.625
- Okay, specifically...
- Mm-hmm.

09:32.625 --> 09:34.667
...you don't know
what you want to do
with your life.

09:34.667 --> 09:37.458
You have no drive,
no real goals,

09:37.458 --> 09:39.375
but somehow
tons of opinions.

09:39.375 --> 09:42.708
Hannah: Interesting,
interesting, interesting,
interesting, interesting.

09:42.708 --> 09:44.917
Why is that interesting
seven times?

09:44.917 --> 09:47.417
I just have to say

09:47.417 --> 09:49.166
that sounds
a lot like you.

09:49.166 --> 09:50.291
Whose side are you on?

09:50.291 --> 09:51.625
She's not on anyone's side.

09:51.625 --> 09:53.000
She's the Dr. Phil.

09:53.000 --> 09:54.667
Well, it's easy to say
when she's on your side.

09:54.667 --> 09:56.500
- I'm not on anyone's side.
- ( mocking gibberish )

09:56.500 --> 09:58.000
I'm not on anyone's side.

09:58.000 --> 09:59.542
( whispering )
I'm on your side.

09:59.542 --> 10:01.708
If I had to pick a side,
it would be your side.

10:01.708 --> 10:03.500
This is something
I'm doing for us.

10:03.500 --> 10:05.250
Why are you whispering?
She can hear you.

10:05.250 --> 10:08.667
I can hear you.
I'm sitting right here.

10:08.667 --> 10:13.583
- What is that?
- This is a space cigarette,
invented by Stephen Dorff.

10:13.583 --> 10:15.291
It's just water vapor
and nicotine

10:15.291 --> 10:17.542
and good things
like that, you know?

10:17.542 --> 10:20.417
I'm really on a mission
to improve myself.

10:20.417 --> 10:22.417
Okay, if you're serious
about improving yourself,

10:22.417 --> 10:24.875
you need to do more
than just, like, smoke
Dorff cigarettes.

10:24.875 --> 10:27.375
You need to,
like, grocery shop
and condition your hair,

10:27.375 --> 10:29.583
even though
I know it does so well
with natural oils.

10:29.583 --> 10:31.000
Jessa:
I'm gonna get that job.

10:31.000 --> 10:33.125
Are you sure
that's the kind of job
you should be having?

10:33.125 --> 10:35.583
Like, being near things
that children are near?

10:35.583 --> 10:39.333
Yeah, I want something
with a touch of innocence.

10:41.041 --> 10:43.500
Shoshanna:
You have a criminal record!

10:44.708 --> 10:45.834
Adam:
No, I'm not like you.

10:45.834 --> 10:47.750
I'm not a different person
every other week.

10:47.750 --> 10:49.250
- Oh, really?
- You're hearing each other.

10:49.250 --> 10:51.250
- Let's keep doing that.
- Really? Oh, what is it?

10:51.250 --> 10:53.333
Okay, it was
an actor last week.

10:53.333 --> 10:54.750
What was it before that,
a woodworker, huh?

10:54.750 --> 10:56.041
And the last time
I saw you, you were, what,

10:56.041 --> 10:58.959
you were gonna go join
the special armed forces,
G.I. Joe?

10:58.959 --> 11:00.667
- Those are professions.
- That's crazy.

11:00.667 --> 11:03.375
I remain the same,
whereas you move to Montana,

11:03.375 --> 11:07.083
put on a phony accent,
and claim to be a midwife
or some shit.

11:07.083 --> 11:08.750
It was a doula.

11:08.750 --> 11:11.250
You know what, guys?
Let's just take
a breath, okay?

11:11.250 --> 11:13.708
Adam, we have given you
a chance to express

11:13.708 --> 11:15.583
what some of your issues
with Caroline are.

11:15.583 --> 11:18.083
So, why don't we now
take a moment to hear
Caroline?

11:18.083 --> 11:20.583
You are doing
really good.

11:20.583 --> 11:23.041
Thank you.
I feel good about it,
but it's too soon to say.

11:23.041 --> 11:26.083
Okay, first I want to say, Adam,
that I love you very much.

11:26.083 --> 11:28.083
- Oh.
- However...

11:28.083 --> 11:30.959
it really upsets me
that he thinks of me

11:30.959 --> 11:33.583
as this insane,
dependent nightmare

11:33.583 --> 11:35.041
because he knows
how hard

11:35.041 --> 11:37.250
I have been trying
to get my stuff together.

11:37.250 --> 11:39.708
Things fell apart
because of bad luck
and you're the victim again,

11:39.708 --> 11:42.166
- but next year--
- Yes, yes, I am cursed
with bad luck.

11:42.166 --> 11:44.041
- I am sorry that
that upsets you so much.
- Over and over.

11:44.041 --> 11:46.750
Just get a normal job
and an apartment like
everybody else

11:46.750 --> 11:48.083
and stop bloodsucking.

11:48.083 --> 11:50.542
He's been angry
like this always at me.

11:50.542 --> 11:52.792
Yeah, yeah.
I know, I know.

11:55.291 --> 11:57.458
I think it is
possibly because

11:57.458 --> 12:01.166
he is internally battling
a sexual desire for me.

12:01.166 --> 12:03.125
Holy dogshit!

12:03.125 --> 12:05.333
That's a weird one.
That's a weird one for me.

12:05.333 --> 12:08.750
I'm sorry, guys.
It doesn't take
a psychiatrist

12:08.750 --> 12:11.333
to correlate Adam's
romantic interest in you

12:11.333 --> 12:13.458
with a repressed
fantasy toward me.

12:13.458 --> 12:14.959
I don't want
to fuck my sister.

12:14.959 --> 12:16.083
No one
is saying you do.

12:16.083 --> 12:17.792
( stomps foot )
Caroline just did.

12:17.792 --> 12:19.417
That is true,
and, Caroline,

12:19.417 --> 12:21.291
that goes in the category
of things we should never

12:21.291 --> 12:22.750
say out loud ever,
no matter what.

12:22.750 --> 12:25.500
This is what she does.
She finds a way to drive
a wedge between people

12:25.500 --> 12:27.041
so everybody ends up
just as unhappy as she is.

12:27.041 --> 12:28.625
I know, I know.
I don't want a wedge
between us.

12:28.625 --> 12:30.125
- She's sick in the brain.
- You're sick!

12:30.125 --> 12:32.417
You're sick in the brain!
You're sick-- ( screaming )

12:32.417 --> 12:34.041
Hannah:
Stop it, you guys!

12:34.041 --> 12:35.959
Please stop!

12:35.959 --> 12:39.333
- Please! Hey! Hey!
- Aha.

12:39.333 --> 12:41.458
Hey, T.O.!
You're nuts!

12:41.458 --> 12:42.959
( laughs )

12:42.959 --> 12:44.917
I do not understand
why you can't

12:44.917 --> 12:47.750
be a little bit better
to each other.

12:47.750 --> 12:50.500
Being an only child
is extremely lonely.

12:50.500 --> 12:53.166
All I wanted as a kid
was a sibling.

12:53.166 --> 12:54.333
Caroline, come on,
you don't think

12:54.333 --> 12:57.000
your brother wants
to have sex with you.

12:57.000 --> 12:59.125
No, not
in a physical way, no.

12:59.125 --> 13:02.583
See, it was all
a big misunderstanding,
all right?

13:02.583 --> 13:05.291
